DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$a=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$b=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$c=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);

BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
If the curve \(y=f(x),\;a \le x \le b,\) is rotated about the horizontal line \(y=c,\) where \(f(x) \le c,\) then one can prove that a formula for the area of the resulting surface is
\[S = \int_{a}^{\,b} {2\pi [c-f(x)] \sqrt{1+[f'(x)]^2}}\, dx.\]

$PAR$HR$PAR
Find the area of the surface generated by rotating the circle \(x^2+y^2=r^2\) about the line \(y=r.\)

$PAR
Surface area = \{ans_rule(30)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp("4*pi^2*r^2", var=>["r"], limits=>[[0,10]]));

ENDDOCUMENT();
